# Stack Rules

## Package Manager: Bun
- Always use `bun` — never `npm`, `npx`, or `yarn`
- Install packages: `bun add [package]`
- Run scripts: `bun run dev`, `bun run build`
- Execute one-off commands: `bunx --bun [command]`
- shadcn component installs: `bunx --bun shadcn@latest add [component]`

## Linter: Biome
- Biome replaces ESLint and Prettier — do not install or configure either
- Biome handles both linting and formatting in one tool
- Do not add `.eslintrc`, `.prettierrc`, or related config files
- If a lint fix is needed, run `bunx biome check --apply .`

## Next.js App Router
- Default to Server Components — only add `"use client"` when you actually need browser APIs, event handlers, or hooks
- Never `"use client"` at the layout level — push it down to the smallest component that needs it
- Data fetching: fetch in Server Components and pass data down as props. Don't fetch in Client Components unless it's truly client-side dynamic data
- Use `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx` at the route level — don't reinvent loading/error UI per-component
- Route handlers go in `app/api/` — keep them thin, logic goes in `lib/`
- `metadata` export for every page — title and description minimum

## TypeScript
- No `any` — if you don't know the type, use `unknown` and narrow it
- Define types/interfaces in `types/` or co-located with the module they belong to
- Props interfaces named `[ComponentName]Props`
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions and intersections
- Don't suppress TypeScript errors with `@ts-ignore` — fix the type issue

## File & Folder Structure
```
src/
  app/              → routes and layouts only
  components/       → shared UI components
    ui/             → shadcn/ui components (don't manually edit these)
  lib/              → utilities, helpers, constants
  hooks/            → custom React hooks
  types/            → shared TypeScript types
  styles/           → global styles only
```

## Tailwind
- Use Tailwind classes, not inline styles
- No arbitrary values unless the design system genuinely requires it — prefer the scale
- Extract repeated class combinations into a component, not a custom CSS class
- `cn()` utility (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional class names — always

## Component Patterns
- One component per file
- File name = component name (PascalCase)
- Export as named export AND default export
- Keep components focused — if a component does more than one thing, split it
- Co-locate component-specific types, hooks, and helpers in the same file unless they're shared

## Data Fetching
- `@tanstack/react-query` for client-side data fetching and caching
- Server Actions for mutations (form submissions, data updates)
- Never `useEffect` + `fetch` for initial data load — use React Query or Server Components
- Loading and error states are required for every query

## Performance
- Images: always use `next/image` — never a raw `<img>` tag
- Links: always `next/link` — never a raw `<a>` for internal navigation
- Fonts: always `next/font` — never a manual Google Fonts `<link>`
- Dynamic imports for heavy components that aren't needed on initial load

## Dependencies
- Check if something can be done with what's already installed before adding a new package
- Ask before adding any new dependency — each one has a cost
- Prefer smaller, focused packages over large frameworks
- Always use `bun add` — never `npm install`
